default-case.description:
Description

This rule aims to requiredefaultcase inswitchstatements. You may optionally include a// no defaultafter the lastcaseif there is nodefaultcase. The comment may be in any desired case, such as// No Default.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint default-case: "error"*/

switch (a) {
    case 1:
        /* code */
        break;
}

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint default-case: "error"*/

switch (a) {
    case 1:
        /* code */
        break;

    default:
        /* code */
        break;
}

switch (a) {
    case 1:
        /* code */
        break;

    // no default
}

switch (a) {
    case 1:
        /* code */
        break;

    // No Default
}

default-case.option:
